> I suggest you look up "reductio ad absurdum" in the dictionary.

I did.  He's right.  You're wrong.  From Webster's Ninth New Collegiate
Dictionary, "disproof of a proposition by showing an absurdity to which
it leads  when carried to its logical conclusion."  No other definition
is given, or needed.
